I do have to say that "class collaboration" sounds a lot like "communism with Chinese characteristics", though.

Fuck yeah, got my space AK all ready to go.

Anarcho-syndicalism in the setting (not the reach, the AoFU is located in a neighboring corridor) technically isn't our anarcho-syndicalism; that died in the 1900s and anyone saying otherwise gives the IWW too much credit. It really only came back in the 2400s or so thanks to the fact that it was so radical to the Authority they didn't give a fuck about bothering to regulate it at first, opposed to more "feasible" alternatives they sought to combat the ideological spread of. And it's really more like a tangentially-related thing; Stepanovism is more like the unholy lovechild of pirate politics and anarcho-syndicalism, and nicked the latter's color scheme because it sounded cool. Copyright law is counter-revolutionary.

Turns out that it actually works in space for reasons I have yet to elaborate on that amount to "huh, self-sufficiency is a necessity, we don't actually need states anymore because we've already scienced the shit out of everything." Unrealistic, but I like it nonetheless.
